WEBVTT

01:32.092 --> 01:32.968
What?

01:35.721 --> 01:36.889
Wolf!

01:36.972 --> 01:38.932
-Get out of my way!
-Move!

01:39.016 --> 01:40.017
Lord, save us.

01:43.353 --> 01:46.148
Back. Stay back! Back.

02:11.715 --> 02:13.926
Sweet Mother Divine, save us.

02:20.224 --> 02:21.099
Oh, my God!

02:22.434 --> 02:23.477
No!

02:43.330 --> 02:45.207
You're a Wolfwalker?

02:46.458 --> 02:47.459
Thank you.

03:58.530 --> 04:02.826
Wolf, wolf, kill the wolf
Hunt them far and yonder

04:02.910 --> 04:07.706
Wolf, wolf, kill the wolf
Till all the wolves are done for

04:10.792 --> 04:13.629
See that, Merlyn? Right on the nose.

04:17.382 --> 04:19.635
What are you saying?
I was aiming for the nose.

04:20.177 --> 04:21.720
I'm glad you agree.

04:21.803 --> 04:23.055
Robyn.

04:23.138 --> 04:24.389
Yes, Father?

04:25.432 --> 04:27.851
Busy with your chores, I assume?

04:27.935 --> 04:28.936
Yes, Father.

04:29.436 --> 04:30.562
Practically finished.

04:30.646 --> 04:32.439
Seems you certainly haven't been idle.

04:32.523 --> 04:33.982
Oh, idle, no.

04:34.775 --> 04:37.402
I've been sweeping and dusting, mopping.

04:37.486 --> 04:39.154
Just can't keep up with it.

04:43.909 --> 04:46.954
I wonder what range that wolf poster is.
Fifteen feet?

04:47.037 --> 04:48.622
No way. Twenty at least.

04:49.206 --> 04:51.041
Although, I'm not sure.

04:51.124 --> 04:53.794
I haven't really considered it.
Too busy cleaning.

04:54.294 --> 04:59.007
Robyn, this is our new home. The bucket
and brush are your tools now, not this.

04:59.424 --> 05:01.677
It's so boring
being stuck in here all day.

05:01.760 --> 05:05.180
I should be out on adventures with you,
like we did back in England.

05:05.722 --> 05:08.892
Oh, lass. Lord Protector has strict rules.

05:08.976 --> 05:11.311
No children beyond the walls,
you know that.

05:11.395 --> 05:13.730
The forest is brimming with real wolves,

05:13.814 --> 05:16.024
and it's my job to hunt them down,
not yours.

05:16.108 --> 05:17.317
I'm not afraid of a wolf.

05:17.401 --> 05:18.861
You've never even seen a wolf.

05:18.944 --> 05:20.237
And I'm still not afraid.

05:20.320 --> 05:22.656
Yes, and that's why
I must be afraid for you.

05:29.121 --> 05:30.789
Well, I'll come with you to the gates.

05:30.873 --> 05:32.583
I'll be back before sundown.

05:32.666 --> 05:33.959
Stay indoors.

05:41.884 --> 05:44.052
Time to practice our tracking, Merlyn.

05:44.136 --> 05:45.137
Yes, now.

05:53.645 --> 05:54.771
Pies here!

05:54.855 --> 05:56.523
You find him, I'll follow.

06:13.540 --> 06:15.417
Fish! Fresh fish!

06:17.336 --> 06:18.504
Good work, Merlyn.

06:20.130 --> 06:24.176
Howls the wolf, wolf, wolf
Hears the wolf, wolf, wolf

06:24.259 --> 06:28.222
Run the wolf, wolf, wolf
Flee the wolf, wolf, wolf

06:28.305 --> 06:32.226
Howls the wolf, wolf, wolf
Hears the wolf, wolf, wolf

06:32.309 --> 06:34.019
Run the wolf, wolf, wolf

06:34.102 --> 06:38.440
Get your pickled oysters,
whelks and periwinkles!

06:38.524 --> 06:40.734
Wash it down with a cup of donkey's milk!

06:40.817 --> 06:41.944
Yuck.

06:42.027 --> 06:44.029
-Just two farthings.
-Where's he gone?

06:44.780 --> 06:47.449
Excuse me. Pardon me. Coming through.

06:47.533 --> 06:49.076
Wolf, wolf, wolf

06:49.159 --> 06:53.080
Run the wolf, wolf, wolf
Flee the wolf, wolf, wolf

06:54.623 --> 06:55.916
Robyn.

06:56.792 --> 06:58.752
I was only gonna track you
as far as the gates.

06:58.836 --> 07:00.420
Really? Then what?

07:00.504 --> 07:03.131
Follow me out and slay
the pack of wolves single-handed?

07:03.215 --> 07:04.883
Yeah, but we could hunt them together.

07:04.967 --> 07:07.052
Wolves, bears, dragons, even!

07:07.886 --> 07:09.388
What am I to do with you?

07:11.974 --> 07:15.477
We could climb mountains and
see giants, meet witches who cast spells,

07:15.561 --> 07:17.563
find mermaids and selkies, even.

07:18.438 --> 07:21.066
Love, you and your fanciful stories.

07:21.650 --> 07:24.570
Wolf, wolf
Hears the wolf, wolf, wolf

07:24.653 --> 07:27.614
Howls the wolf, wolf, wolf
Run the wolf--

07:27.698 --> 07:29.157
Howls the wolf

07:29.825 --> 07:31.201
Goodfellowe!

07:31.285 --> 07:33.871
-Soldiers! Leg it!
-Goodfellowe! Come here a minute!

07:33.954 --> 07:35.998
Yes, sir! Stay here, lass.

07:36.081 --> 07:40.419
Shoot the wolf, wolf, wolf!
Hunt the wolf, wolf, wolf!

07:40.502 --> 07:44.298
Get the wolf, wolf, wolf!
Kill the wolf, wolf, wolf!

07:44.381 --> 07:48.468
Shoot the wolf, wolf, wolf!
Hunt the wolf, wolf, wolf!

07:48.552 --> 07:51.471
-Get the wolf, wolf, wolf!
-Got you now, wolf.

07:51.555 --> 07:54.474
Kill the wolf, wolf, wolf!
Shoot the wolf, wolf, wolf!

07:56.268 --> 08:00.355
Hey, English girl. Where do you think
you're going dressed like that?

08:00.439 --> 08:01.815
I'm a hunter.

08:01.899 --> 08:03.483
"I'm a hunter."

08:03.567 --> 08:06.236
Would you listen
to her fancy dancy accent?

08:06.320 --> 08:09.698
I am a hunter. Just like my father.
He's the best hunter there is.

08:09.781 --> 08:12.701
No, he's not. My father's the best hunter.

08:12.784 --> 08:15.746
Yeah? Well, we're hunting wolves
for the Lord Protector.

08:15.829 --> 08:18.707
Lord Protector put my father
in chains for nothing.

08:18.790 --> 08:21.251
You English think you're so great,
but you're not.

08:21.335 --> 08:23.086
You should all just go home.

08:23.170 --> 08:24.755
But first, give us a go on your crossbow.

08:24.838 --> 08:25.964
No!

08:27.674 --> 08:30.219
-You'll pay for that, English girl.
-She pushed him!

08:30.302 --> 08:32.221
You're dead now!

08:36.140 --> 08:38.852
-What's going on here?
-Soldier! Leg it!

08:52.032 --> 08:53.909
Why must you wander off like that, Robyn?

08:53.992 --> 08:56.119
I was trying to help you,
and then there was a boy,

08:56.203 --> 08:57.579
and he said his father
was better than you,

08:57.663 --> 09:00.040
-and then he wanted my crossbow and--
-Robyn!

09:00.123 --> 09:03.001
We are not so welcome in this land yet.

09:03.085 --> 09:07.005
You're better off to stay at home
while I'm working. You're safe there.

09:07.089 --> 09:08.715
But I'd be just as safe
out there with you.

09:08.799 --> 09:10.801
No, Robyn! Stay inside!

09:10.884 --> 09:12.010
Do as you're told.

09:13.554 --> 09:15.180
It's for your own good, Robyn.

09:16.598 --> 09:17.599
Look...

09:18.642 --> 09:21.979
this evening, when I'm back,
you can help me make new arrows.

09:23.105 --> 09:26.859
Tell me your stories of giants
and dragons. Would you like that?

09:26.942 --> 09:28.110
I suppose so.

09:28.193 --> 09:29.611
Now then, be good.

09:38.537 --> 09:41.582
No children beyond the walls.
Lord Protector's orders.

09:46.545 --> 09:50.048
If he could just see how good I am,
what a hunter I am,

09:50.132 --> 09:52.050
then he'd have to let me come along.

09:52.801 --> 09:55.387
What are you, Merlyn?
A falcon or a chicken?

09:59.391 --> 10:01.268
Kill the wolf! Kill the wolf!

10:01.351 --> 10:03.187
Leave me alone!

10:03.270 --> 10:04.646
Get away from me!

10:07.524 --> 10:09.109
Got you now, wolf!

10:11.737 --> 10:14.156
Lads, we got a flag! Come on!

10:14.656 --> 10:16.867
Down with the Lord Protector!

10:18.160 --> 10:20.829
-Stop this at once!
-Get out of here!

10:20.913 --> 10:23.123
-Get that flag!
-Get out of here, quickly!

10:25.042 --> 10:26.752
Go on, you little rebels, you!

10:27.878 --> 10:30.464
Well done!
Well done, boys Run! Run!

11:39.741 --> 11:41.034
Yes, I see it.

11:43.871 --> 11:45.122
I won't step in it.

12:05.225 --> 12:10.397
Help! Wolf! Wolf! Help!

12:10.480 --> 12:11.523
Wolf?

12:11.607 --> 12:15.068
Wolf! Merlyn, quick, fly. Find the wolf.

12:22.201 --> 12:23.827
Wolf!

12:23.911 --> 12:25.287
-Run!
-Get back! Get back!

12:25.370 --> 12:27.289
Run!

12:28.874 --> 12:30.000
Wolves!

12:39.176 --> 12:40.594
Get away! Get back!

12:42.095 --> 12:43.180
Help!

12:45.682 --> 12:47.768
Get back! Get back!

12:49.353 --> 12:51.855
Why, shoot! For God's sake, shoot!

13:05.202 --> 13:06.203
Merlyn!

13:29.434 --> 13:30.435
What?

13:34.314 --> 13:36.483
No! That's my bird! Leave him be!

13:38.443 --> 13:39.486
Stop!

13:53.000 --> 13:54.251
Robyn!

13:59.548 --> 14:01.925
-Robyn!
-Merlyn, he's gone!

14:02.009 --> 14:04.469
-We have to get him back.
-You could've been eaten alive.

14:04.553 --> 14:06.680
What were you thinking?
What are you doing out here?

14:06.763 --> 14:08.682
-I was trying to help you.
-Help me?

14:08.765 --> 14:11.852
I told you, you shouldn't be out here!
This is why!

14:11.935 --> 14:14.771
-Father, they took Merlyn.
-Lass, no.

14:15.314 --> 14:17.191
No, you're not going after him.
Not in there.

14:17.274 --> 14:18.442
But we can't leave him.

14:18.525 --> 14:22.070
Look, I promised your mother
I'd keep you safe.

14:26.825 --> 14:28.076
It's all right, love.

14:29.536 --> 14:31.997
You'll be safe back in the town. Come on.

14:34.583 --> 14:35.918
It's for your own good.

14:51.517 --> 14:54.520
By God, you're one lucky girl.

14:54.603 --> 14:57.356
Did you not see?
'Twas a Wolfwalker, by Crom!

14:57.439 --> 14:58.607
Now calm down, will you.

14:58.690 --> 15:00.817
Everyone knows you
can't be cutting down their woods.

15:00.901 --> 15:02.903
If you do, they'll get you.
Sure, that's the deal.

15:02.986 --> 15:04.488
There's no deal with anyone.

15:04.571 --> 15:09.451
Saint Patrick made it with the old pagans
and you're breaking it, you eejits!

15:09.535 --> 15:11.328
-We need to clear the woods.
-Did you not see?

15:11.411 --> 15:13.121
Actually, I did see the wolf attack.

15:13.205 --> 15:16.083
The way them wolves answered her call.

15:16.166 --> 15:19.378
Them forests is riddled with wolves,
I tell you.

15:19.461 --> 15:21.088
Won't be long before the wolves are gone.

15:21.171 --> 15:24.800
It won't be long before they're
inside the town walls with the hunger.

15:24.883 --> 15:28.011
No. No, we'll tame these lands.
The Lord Protector has ordered it.

15:28.095 --> 15:31.932
Ah, the great Lord Protector.

15:32.015 --> 15:35.561
Renowned for being true to his word.
Hilarious.

15:35.644 --> 15:37.938
At least the old king kept us safe.

15:38.021 --> 15:41.567
He's just an upstart. Lord Protector.

15:41.650 --> 15:44.403
Lord Protector.

15:44.486 --> 15:45.904
Protector of what?

15:45.988 --> 15:47.155
Come here!

15:47.239 --> 15:50.951
If you have grievances,
you should speak with me directly.

15:51.034 --> 15:52.077
What are you doing? No!

15:52.160 --> 15:54.997
-Get your hands off of--
-Hold still!

15:55.080 --> 15:58.125
-Jesus, Mary and Joseph. This is a joke.
-Get in.

15:58.208 --> 16:00.711
Let me out of here!

16:00.794 --> 16:03.922
I did nothing wrong!

16:04.006 --> 16:06.175
By Crom! The devil take your head!

16:06.258 --> 16:09.344
-Another wolf attack?
-Aye, my lord.

16:09.428 --> 16:13.140
A few more like him and we have
another rebellion on our hands.

16:13.223 --> 16:17.728
If we do not clear the trees,
the farmers cannot work the land,

16:17.811 --> 16:21.398
and the woodcutters cannot clear the trees
with these wolves.

16:21.481 --> 16:23.525
-This is not acceptable.
-Aye, my lord.

16:23.609 --> 16:26.778
We must show them
the wolves are no threat.

16:26.862 --> 16:29.281
They're just beasts. Finish them.

16:29.364 --> 16:30.365
Yes, my lord.

16:33.702 --> 16:36.538
And this is your girl, yes?

16:36.622 --> 16:39.208
It is, my lord. Robyn.

16:39.291 --> 16:43.504
There should be no child beyond the walls.
Why is she not in the scullery?

16:43.587 --> 16:45.422
My lord, she doesn't work there.

16:45.506 --> 16:48.884
You! See to it that the girl
reports to the scullery.

16:48.967 --> 16:49.968
Father.

16:50.052 --> 16:52.095
Do as the Lord Protector commands, lass.

16:57.893 --> 17:00.687
I ride out to deal
with the revolt in the south.

17:00.771 --> 17:04.733
When I return, I want all the wolves
gone from this forest.

17:04.816 --> 17:07.778
-Yes, my lord.
-Goodfellowe, you have two days.

17:08.319 --> 17:09.613
Don't waste them.

17:25.295 --> 17:26.922
Hey, girl.

17:27.005 --> 17:30.217
The one who took your bird,
I've seen her before.

17:30.300 --> 17:32.553
A while back with her mammy.

17:32.636 --> 17:36.807
Cross my heart,
she's one of them Wolfwalkers.

17:36.890 --> 17:38.433
Wolfwalkers?

17:38.517 --> 17:40.686
Yeah, Wolfwalkers.

17:40.769 --> 17:45.774
The ones that can talk to wolves, like.
But you know, they can heal as well.

17:45.858 --> 17:49.069
Her mother healed me with some wild magic.

17:49.152 --> 17:52.823
Maybe she'll fix your bird up.
Maybe she'll eat him.

17:52.906 --> 17:56.201
-I don't know.
-I need to get him back.

17:56.285 --> 17:59.788
I'd say once we're behind them walls,
neither of us is going anywhere.

18:03.625 --> 18:05.252
Can you keep a secret?

18:08.463 --> 18:09.798
My sheep.

18:11.383 --> 18:13.844
Lads, you didn't
lock that gate right at all.

18:13.927 --> 18:15.137
You let them sheep out, didn't you?

18:15.220 --> 18:18.974
Oh, yeah. Blame me for that too.
Everything is Seán Óg's fault!

18:19.057 --> 18:20.726
Get back in the cart, you.

18:20.809 --> 18:22.769
I feel like stretching my legs!

18:24.688 --> 18:26.857
-Help me with my sheep, you langers!
-I'll show them out!

18:26.940 --> 18:28.734
Oi! Get him!

18:29.568 --> 18:32.571
Hey, whatever your name is,
get back in that cart!

18:32.654 --> 18:33.906
Round up those sheep.

18:33.989 --> 18:35.949
Off of me! Have you no manners at all?

18:36.700 --> 18:38.202
Get back in there, you!

18:38.285 --> 18:39.870
An extra week in the stocks for that.

18:39.953 --> 18:41.747
-Where's the girl gone?
-Don't see her.

18:41.830 --> 18:43.123
Maybe in the woods.

18:43.207 --> 18:46.627
You two, look out for a girl.
She ran into the forest.

18:46.710 --> 18:49.963
Get her and bring her back to the castle.
Lord Protector's orders.

18:50.047 --> 18:51.548
-Yes, sir.
-Devil take--

18:53.091 --> 18:57.095
English soldiers. Who do they think
they are? Bossing us around.

18:57.179 --> 18:59.014
-What was that?
-Nothing!

18:59.097 --> 19:00.224
Get a move on!

19:00.307 --> 19:01.350
Yes, sir!

19:08.106 --> 19:11.151
Merlyn? Merlyn!

19:13.403 --> 19:15.489
Wolf, wolf
Kill the wolf

19:15.572 --> 19:18.325
Hunt them far and yonder

19:18.408 --> 19:20.702
Wolf, wolf
Kill the wolf

19:21.411 --> 19:24.039
Till all the wolves are done for

19:39.805 --> 19:41.014
Merlyn?

19:43.767 --> 19:44.810
Merlyn!

19:47.938 --> 19:49.022
Merlyn!

19:50.107 --> 19:53.527
Look at you. You're good as new,
aren't you? How's that?

19:54.278 --> 19:55.946
I'm so glad you're not hurt.

19:56.029 --> 19:59.491
How did they heal your wing?
It was that girl, wasn't it?

20:00.284 --> 20:03.704
What did she do?
Oh, I was afraid she was gonna eat you.

20:13.422 --> 20:16.091
Stay back, now! Back! I'll shoot!

20:16.175 --> 20:18.343
Merlyn. Merlyn, what are you doing?

20:19.052 --> 20:22.014
Get away, wolf! I swear, I'll--

20:22.681 --> 20:26.310
Merlyn, stop that! No! Wha--

20:26.393 --> 20:28.562
Stay away, wolf.

20:28.645 --> 20:30.689
No. Get away.

20:31.690 --> 20:34.776
No! Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.

20:39.781 --> 20:43.660
Get back! I'm gonna get you!
Get away, wolf!

21:32.751 --> 21:33.752
Merlyn?

21:36.296 --> 21:38.298
Merlyn! Wait!

21:38.382 --> 21:39.591
Merlyn!

21:56.149 --> 21:57.317
Merlyn!

22:02.281 --> 22:03.282
Merlyn!

22:41.820 --> 22:43.155
Whoa!

23:38.377 --> 23:39.378
Merlyn?

24:03.277 --> 24:04.319
What?

24:36.894 --> 24:42.107
You can come out now.
We can smell you. Yeah, you stink.

24:42.191 --> 24:44.693
I knew you were here.
Come out of your hidey-hole.

24:44.776 --> 24:46.278
Let's see you.

24:51.283 --> 24:52.868
Don't kill me.

24:52.951 --> 24:54.995
I do what I like. Come here.

24:55.078 --> 24:57.247
You're a--

24:57.331 --> 25:00.959
A Wolfwalker. So what?
You should thank me.

25:01.043 --> 25:02.961
-Why?
-I saved your life.

25:03.045 --> 25:04.796
Saved me? You bit me!

25:04.880 --> 25:06.882
Well, you kicked me
in the gob enough times.

25:06.965 --> 25:08.258
Well, you were attacking me.

25:08.342 --> 25:10.636
I was trying to get you out of that trap.

25:10.719 --> 25:13.263
And anyway, you came into my woods.

25:13.347 --> 25:15.182
Your woods? They're our woods.

25:15.265 --> 25:17.518
Your wolves are attacking the woodcutters
and the sheep.

25:17.601 --> 25:22.064
They should be staying closer to the town
and so should you, townie.

25:22.147 --> 25:23.565
Now give us a look at you.

25:24.608 --> 25:26.735
-Are you seeing things?
-Get off me!

25:26.818 --> 25:28.695
-How's your smell?
-Stop it!

25:28.779 --> 25:30.906
Smells like townie. Any extra fur?

25:30.989 --> 25:32.741
That's mine! Get away!

25:32.824 --> 25:36.662
Now, stop moving and let me fix it
before it's too late.

25:36.745 --> 25:37.955
Hey, get off me!

25:38.038 --> 25:40.499
Will you stop? Let me fix it!

25:41.959 --> 25:42.960
Fine.

25:57.850 --> 25:58.851
But what?

26:00.269 --> 26:03.272
Well, fixed now. Never happened.
Off you go.

26:03.355 --> 26:04.565
You did heal Merlyn.

26:04.648 --> 26:08.485
Yeah. I fixed you and your bird
and saved your life.

26:08.569 --> 26:10.612
You're welcome, townie. Bye!

26:10.696 --> 26:11.822
No, wait. Who's that?

26:11.905 --> 26:14.741
Is she your... your mother?

26:14.825 --> 26:16.994
You better go or the wolves will eat you.

26:17.411 --> 26:19.162
What? But I don't--

26:19.246 --> 26:21.415
Oh, no. Too late. They're gonna eat you!

26:21.498 --> 26:22.499
No!

26:29.590 --> 26:30.841
Whoa!

26:42.269 --> 26:45.898
Run away, townie girl!
The wolves are after you!

26:45.981 --> 26:47.733
Can't get away from us, townie!

26:48.317 --> 26:49.693
Get away from me!

26:49.776 --> 26:52.279
But you're so slow.

26:52.362 --> 26:56.241
Scared of your shadows, you are.
What would a townie know about wolves?

26:56.325 --> 26:58.368
Why do you have so much stuff?

26:58.452 --> 27:00.704
Hey, stop! That's my gear for hunting!

27:00.787 --> 27:03.415
Oh, a hunter. A little girl like you?

27:03.498 --> 27:05.125
Well, you're a girl too.

27:05.209 --> 27:07.377
I'm no girl! I'm a Wolfwalker!

27:08.545 --> 27:09.671
Whoa!

27:09.755 --> 27:11.089
Up you go!

27:12.299 --> 27:14.801
When I sleeps, I'm a wolf.

27:14.885 --> 27:19.389
When I'm awake, I'm me, Mebh!
Mebh Óg MacTire!

27:19.890 --> 27:21.183
What's your name, anyway?

27:21.642 --> 27:23.101
-Robyn.
-Robyn?

27:23.894 --> 27:27.731
I like birdies.
I climb so high to catch them.

27:27.814 --> 27:30.943
I'm too smart for them, though.
They can't get away from me for long.

27:40.869 --> 27:43.580
Caught again. Some hunter.

27:44.665 --> 27:47.042
That's two for me, none for you.

27:47.125 --> 27:48.752
Whoa!

27:49.503 --> 27:53.382
Stop being so annoying.
It's not funny, you know.

27:53.465 --> 27:54.842
Let me down!

27:54.925 --> 27:56.885
All right, townie.

27:56.969 --> 27:58.637
If you say so.

27:58.720 --> 27:59.805
No, wait!

28:04.726 --> 28:06.478
Stop calling me "townie."

28:06.562 --> 28:09.898
All right, Robyn.
Back home with you. Fun's over.

28:09.982 --> 28:13.151
Well, Mebh Ogamacatemera, your idea--

28:13.235 --> 28:15.195
-Do you hear that?
-What?

28:15.279 --> 28:17.531
A man. I'll get rid of him.

28:17.614 --> 28:20.242
A man? Oh, no. Father.

28:31.628 --> 28:34.298
Just one townie.
I'll give him a bit of a scare.

28:34.381 --> 28:35.716
No, stop.

29:17.299 --> 29:18.842
That was too close.

29:18.926 --> 29:23.096
What are you so scared of?
We have a pack of wolves with us.

29:27.059 --> 29:28.852
Hey, I told you.

29:28.936 --> 29:34.024
You can't go out in the daytime.
Mammy said so. Go back to bed.

29:34.566 --> 29:36.026
Is that your mummy back in the cave?

29:36.109 --> 29:38.779
Of course! Sure don't I look like her?

29:38.862 --> 29:42.616
And are any of the other wolves
people too?

29:42.699 --> 29:45.494
No. Jeepers! Are you mad?

29:45.577 --> 29:47.579
How big do you think my family is?

29:48.789 --> 29:51.667
I'm not supposed to be out here.
Listen, I've got to get back.

29:51.750 --> 29:54.795
Great, I'm mad to get rid of you.
Close your eyes.

29:54.878 --> 29:55.879
What? Why?

29:55.963 --> 29:58.799
Don't want you coming
back to my den. It's secret.

30:00.425 --> 30:01.593
But I already found it.

30:01.677 --> 30:03.387
Just shut up and walk.

30:03.470 --> 30:05.013
I'll point you back to the town.

30:05.097 --> 30:07.140
No, I need my crossbow back first.

30:07.224 --> 30:09.476
What do you need that for?
Shooting your bird again?

30:09.560 --> 30:11.019
No, shooting...

30:11.728 --> 30:13.230
Never mind.

30:13.313 --> 30:15.649
This way, hunter-townie-Robyn-girl.

30:20.946 --> 30:22.906
Hey! Stop pushing so fast.

30:22.990 --> 30:24.575
Will you stop complaining?

30:30.539 --> 30:31.540
Smell that?

30:32.040 --> 30:33.041
Mebh.

30:36.295 --> 30:38.005
Town tasties.

30:38.589 --> 30:40.048
"Town tasties"?

30:41.758 --> 30:44.052
What? Where's she gone now?

30:46.680 --> 30:48.182
What did you tell them?

30:48.265 --> 30:50.684
Just she's going home, isn't she?
'Tis obvious.

30:50.767 --> 30:54.271
Ned, say if that wolf bit her, like,
could she turn into one of them?

30:54.354 --> 30:55.189
A wolf?

30:55.272 --> 30:59.026
No. One of them half-wolf,
half-witch, half-people?

30:59.109 --> 31:01.862
Wolfwalkers? Will you stop?

31:01.945 --> 31:05.115
We are cutting down their woods, Ned.
Shouldn't be doing it.

31:05.199 --> 31:07.201
Save me from that nonsense.

31:07.284 --> 31:09.328
Seán Óg and the soldiers making us.

31:09.411 --> 31:13.749
But if old Lord Ironside
doesn't sort out those wolves,

31:13.832 --> 31:17.377
it won't just be us
who'll stop taking his orders.

31:17.461 --> 31:19.588
No more orders for me, Ned.

31:19.671 --> 31:21.798
Those town tasties are mine.

31:21.882 --> 31:24.718
I'm not after that.
I need my crossbow back.

31:25.385 --> 31:28.722
Oh. All right.
But those town tasties are mine.

31:28.805 --> 31:32.809
-No stuck-up lord in our city again.
-No, we won't, Ned.

31:34.061 --> 31:35.604
-What?
-What is it, Ned?

31:35.687 --> 31:36.813
The wind, maybe.

31:38.565 --> 31:40.651
Hey, what did you do with the spuds?

31:41.068 --> 31:44.196
The spuds, Ned? Hey, the bread's gone too.

31:44.279 --> 31:46.698
No spuds and no bread?

31:46.782 --> 31:49.868
-My hat. Give me my hat.
-My bread. Give me that.

31:50.577 --> 31:52.704
There's someone in there! What the...

31:52.788 --> 31:54.081
My milk!

31:54.164 --> 31:55.541
Something took my milk!

31:55.624 --> 31:57.251
Go! Go! Go!

32:03.465 --> 32:04.967
They nearly caught us.

32:07.803 --> 32:10.472
Nobody can catch me, townie.

32:13.183 --> 32:16.645
How can you stand living in there?
All the smells.

32:18.272 --> 32:19.857
It is pretty smelly.

32:20.899 --> 32:22.985
I don't like being stuck in there.

32:23.569 --> 32:25.112
I miss England.

32:25.195 --> 32:27.447
What's an "England"?

32:27.531 --> 32:28.782
I used to live there.

32:28.866 --> 32:31.952
I could go wherever I wanted,
play with my friends.

32:32.035 --> 32:33.328
It was really nice.

32:33.412 --> 32:35.247
Sounds like the forest.

32:35.330 --> 32:38.959
Merlyn and I even used to help Father
hunt for food.

32:39.042 --> 32:41.879
Now he wants me to stay in town
all the time.

32:41.962 --> 32:44.882
Stay here in the forest. It's great.

32:45.549 --> 32:47.759
-Loads of running.
-Playing.

32:47.843 --> 32:49.761
Eating, messing, climbing.

32:50.721 --> 32:51.722
Free.

32:54.224 --> 32:57.102
I can't. I can't leave my father.

32:57.561 --> 33:00.063
He has to work for the Lord Protector
and--

33:00.939 --> 33:04.276
Mebh, you can't stay in the forest either.
They're cutting it all down.

33:04.359 --> 33:06.528
No way! I'll scare them off.

33:06.612 --> 33:10.073
The Lord Protector wants the wolves gone.
Dead! You have to leave.

33:10.157 --> 33:13.827
We were leaving. Me, Mammy, with the pack.

33:13.911 --> 33:14.912
What stopped you?

33:15.537 --> 33:17.539
-Mammy went off.
-As a wolf?

33:17.623 --> 33:20.417
Yeah, to find us a new place to live.

33:20.501 --> 33:26.381
I'm sure it's some huge den
with no stinkers around and loads of food.

33:26.465 --> 33:29.968
It's going to be amazing!

33:30.052 --> 33:33.472
So then, where is she?
Do you think she got caught?

33:33.555 --> 33:37.059
No. She's fine. Nobody can catch my mammy.

33:37.142 --> 33:41.939
And anyway, if she was caught by those
stinkers, I'd get my wolves to eat them!

33:42.022 --> 33:44.650
So, you're waiting for her to come back?

33:45.234 --> 33:46.276
Yep.

33:46.985 --> 33:52.032
It's just her and me in the whole world.

33:53.909 --> 33:55.202
Like me and Father.

34:02.167 --> 34:03.460
But what if they find the den?

34:03.544 --> 34:05.921
No, they won't. Nobody has.

34:06.004 --> 34:07.005
Well, I did.

34:07.089 --> 34:09.550
Yeah. Only 'cause I let you.

34:26.525 --> 34:28.110
I have to tell my father about you.

34:28.193 --> 34:31.196
He didn't know--
We didn't know that Wolfwalkers are real.

34:34.324 --> 34:37.870
That you were people. I better get back.

34:41.915 --> 34:43.375
Look, I'm gonna help you.

34:43.458 --> 34:45.127
Wait for me at the big tree tomorrow.

34:45.210 --> 34:49.172
I'll bring you some bread--
I mean, some "town tasties."

34:49.255 --> 34:52.134
All right so. Smell you later, townie.

34:52.217 --> 34:53.969
Not if I smell you first.

35:21.121 --> 35:22.998
'Tis yourself.

35:24.750 --> 35:26.835
So, they didn't eat you? That's great.

35:26.919 --> 35:29.421
You were right. That girl healed Merlyn.

35:29.505 --> 35:32.299
Didn't she, now? I told you.

35:32.382 --> 35:33.383
I better get back.

35:33.467 --> 35:37.137
So, you'll know where to find me anyways
if you're looking for me.

35:39.473 --> 35:40.474
Father?

35:41.767 --> 35:42.768
Father?

35:43.477 --> 35:45.062
I've got to convince him.

35:45.771 --> 35:48.273
We need to tidy this place up
before he gets back.

35:57.324 --> 35:59.743
"My, Robyn, this place is sparkling."

36:00.619 --> 36:03.038
Thank you, Father.
Take a seat. Put up your feet.

36:03.580 --> 36:05.249
"Don't mind if I do, lass."

36:05.332 --> 36:06.500
Hard day hunting?

36:06.583 --> 36:09.044
"Aye. Not a sniff of wolf out there."

36:09.837 --> 36:13.131
Well, what if I told you
I can get all the wolves to leave

36:13.215 --> 36:14.883
and we don't even have to kill them?

36:15.384 --> 36:17.427
"I'd say you're telling tall tales again."

36:17.511 --> 36:20.430
Oh, but I'm not.
Now, promise me you won't get angry.

36:20.514 --> 36:21.682
"I promise."

36:21.765 --> 36:25.269
You see, I met a girl in the forest
who has magic healing powers.

36:25.352 --> 36:26.562
She healed Merlyn.

36:27.729 --> 36:29.273
And she's a Wolfwalker.

36:29.857 --> 36:31.108
"A Wolfwalker?"

36:31.525 --> 36:34.903
It's true. When she sleeps,
she turns into a wolf.

36:34.987 --> 36:36.363
She can talk to the wolves.

36:36.446 --> 36:38.448
Her and her mother were
going to take the wolves away,

36:38.532 --> 36:41.535
-but her mother went missing.
-"Missing? Poor thing."

36:41.618 --> 36:44.121
I know, but if we can
help her find her mother,

36:44.204 --> 36:45.956
then they can
all leave the forest together,

36:46.039 --> 36:48.458
and you will have done your duty
to the Lord Protector.

36:48.542 --> 36:51.170
"Oh, brilliant, lass.
Absolutely brilliant.

36:51.253 --> 36:52.963
Thank you. Our problems are solved.

36:53.046 --> 36:55.132
We can go back to how things used to be."

37:00.220 --> 37:02.181
My girl, come here to me.

37:02.764 --> 37:06.351
Are you all right? How are you
after that wolf attack? A bit shaken?

37:06.435 --> 37:08.437
No, I'm fine.
Take a seat. Put up your feet.

37:10.230 --> 37:11.273
That's nice.

37:11.940 --> 37:15.277
And how was your scullery work?
You must be tired, love.

37:15.360 --> 37:17.529
Well, about that.
What if I told you I could--

37:17.613 --> 37:21.158
And Merlyn is back.
My, you've had quite the day, lass.

37:21.241 --> 37:23.285
Yes, I have. But what if I told you--

37:23.368 --> 37:24.703
My day has been awful.

37:24.786 --> 37:27.664
Every trap I set this week
has either been broken or sprung.

37:27.748 --> 37:29.208
Never seen the like of these wolves.

37:29.291 --> 37:32.711
Father, what if I told you
I can get all the wolves to leave

37:32.794 --> 37:34.630
and you don't even have to kill them?

37:34.713 --> 37:36.924
Now, promise you won't get angry with me.

37:37.007 --> 37:38.008
Go on.

37:38.467 --> 37:39.510
You didn't promise.

37:39.593 --> 37:41.303
I know. Go on. Tell me.

37:41.845 --> 37:45.557
-You see, I went back to find Merlyn--
-You were out in the woods?

37:45.641 --> 37:47.267
Father, listen. She's one of them.

37:47.351 --> 37:49.853
A Wolfwalker,
like the woodcutter said. They're real!

37:49.937 --> 37:51.438
-You went back?
-But, Father--

37:51.522 --> 37:52.523
You left the scullery?

37:52.606 --> 37:54.900
Well, I didn't actually
get to the scullery.

37:54.983 --> 37:57.194
What? The Lord Protector ordered--

37:57.277 --> 37:58.820
-If we can just find her mother and--
-Listen!

37:58.904 --> 38:01.448
You have to follow
the Lord Protector's rules.

38:01.532 --> 38:03.867
He gave you a direct order
and you disobeyed him.

38:03.951 --> 38:05.619
Have you no fear of the stocks?

38:06.453 --> 38:09.122
We need to work together
to stay in this town, lass.

38:09.206 --> 38:11.083
I'll bring you to the scullery
tomorrow myself.

38:11.166 --> 38:13.377
But please,
I thought you would understand.

38:14.044 --> 38:15.546
I can help you. If we just--

38:15.629 --> 38:20.217
Help me by doing your work
and staying in town, away from danger.

38:20.801 --> 38:21.927
Now, promise me.

38:23.387 --> 38:24.429
I promise, Father.

38:24.972 --> 38:26.557
All right. Now, go to your bed.

38:31.270 --> 38:32.938
Mother would have listened to me.

38:34.481 --> 38:36.525
She would have wanted you safe, Robyn.

38:37.818 --> 38:38.819
Sleep well.

38:45.033 --> 38:46.910
We'll find a way to help her, Merlyn.

39:27.618 --> 39:29.828
-Robyn?
-Father?

39:29.912 --> 39:32.748
-You all right?
-It's nothing.

39:32.831 --> 39:34.208
Just a bad dream.

39:34.291 --> 39:38.712
Well, should make an early start of it,
both of us. Let's go.

39:59.650 --> 40:02.277
Nice to have a new girl joining us.

40:02.361 --> 40:03.695
-Keep an eye on her.
-Aye.

40:03.779 --> 40:05.447
-She's to work the full day.
-Aye, aye.

40:05.531 --> 40:07.783
-Work is prayer, Robyn.
-'Tis all right, child.

40:07.866 --> 40:10.744
Sure wasn't I only half your age
when I started here.

40:10.827 --> 40:13.288
Just do what you're told now,
and you'll be grand.

40:14.164 --> 40:15.874
It's for your own good, lass.

40:48.991 --> 40:51.076
Work is prayer, girl.

40:51.159 --> 40:52.870
Better if you don't stop.

41:19.563 --> 41:20.772
